SourceString: Absorb the Nemesis Energy within the Tortured Priest.
I absorbed the Nemesis Energy from within the Tortured Priest.
I encountered a Priest of Kronos, tortured by Nemesis\'s power in an ancient temple.
I freed a Priest of Kronos who was tortured by Nemesis\'s power, and he revealed that Nemesis seeks to raise Kronos.
Convince the Tortured Priest to release his Nemesis Energy
Absorb the Nemesis Energy within the Tortured Priest
Absorb the Nemesis Energy within the Deranged Priest.
I absorbed the Nemesis Energy from within the Deranged Priest.
I came upon a Priest of Kronos who must have managed to survive within the temple for centuries. Nemesis seems to have filled him with her divine energy.
I came upon a Priest of Kronos who gave Nemesis the knowledge of how to use Titan Ichor to raise Kronos, and in return she filled him with her dark energy.
Absorb the Nemesis Energy from within the Deranged Priest
Absorb the Nemesis Energy from the shrine
Investigate the inscription on the stone
Absorb major Nemesis Energies within the ruined Temple of Kronos.
I absorbed Nemesis Energies within the Temple of Kronos.
Glaukos told me that the ruined Temple of Kronos contains a concentration of Nemesis\'s power. I should delve into the ruin and absorb all I can.
The Temple of Kronos contained more than just Nemesis Energy for me to absorb--forbidden lore about how to raise Kronos was hidden there.
Find a major Nemesis Energy within the temple
Absorb Nemesis Energy at the dig site
I used the dye phial to absorb Nemesis Energy
The Moirai gave me a powerful gift; a divine dye phial that I can use to absorb energy Nemesis left behind. Glaukos told me of an ichthian dig site where I can try it out.
I used the dye phial to absorb Nemesis Energy, and discovered that doing so connects my mind to Nemesis\'s for a brief time.
Absorb the minor Nemesis Energy at the small dig site
Absorb the minor Nemesis Energy at the old siren nest
Absorb the minor Nemesis Energy at the seaside fort
Explore the center of the dig site
Absorb the Nemesis Energy at the heart of the Ichthian Stronghold
I absorbed the Nemesis Energy at the Ichthian Stronghold
Glaukos sensed a major source of Nemesis Energy right at the heart of the ichthian\'s military power. Despite the danger, I\'ll need to find it.
I fought my way into the Ichthian Stronghold, defeated their king, and absorbed the Nemesis Energy.
Find a way around the fortifications
Open the path through the ruins
Fight your way to the heart of the stronghold
Absorb the Nemesis Energy within the statue
I found Glaukos and he helped interpret the Moirai\'s prophecy
The Moirai gave me a powerful gift and a mysterious prophecy, telling me that finding Glaukos would help make my next steps clear.
Talking to Glaukos made my next step clear: I need to test out my new Dye Phial by absorbing Nemesis Energy at the Ichthian Dig Site.
Reach the Northern Beaches beyond the Moirai Temple
Find Glaukos in the Northern Beaches
Find Glaukos at the Travelers\' Refuge
Absorb the Nemesis Energy within Skylla
I absorbed the Nemesis Energy within Skylla
It\'s time to face Skylla. The monster she\'s become will put up a strong fight, but if I use the dye phial to absorb the Nemesis Energy corrupting her, she should turn back into a nymph.
I freed Skylla, but Nemesis appeared and killed Glaukos. The dye phial protected me from direct attacks from her, but this is far from over.
Open the portal to the Sunken Temple
Find Skylla and absorb the Nemesis Energy within her
Find the other lever and activate it
Absorb the Nemesis Energy within Skylla
Flee through the portal to Olympos
Ensure Anaxis gets safely back to camp
I helped Anaxis get safely to camp
Captain Theras asked me to keep an eye out for Anaxis, the ship\'s engineer and the only one who could build the crew a new vessel to sail home in.
I found Anaxis trapped in a haunted prison, but helped him escape and make it back to camp so he can build the shipwrecked crew a new ship.
Defeat the restless dead blocking the exit
Talk to Anaxis and Theras back at camp
Captain Theras asked me to keep an eye out for Anaxis, the ship\'s engineer and the only one who could build the crew a new vessel to sail home in.
I encountered a man named Anaxis in a haunted prison. He asked for my help to escape back to the surface.
I encountered a giant, talking turtle as I was exploring the beaches.
I navigated the Grotto of Cursed Treasure to get a cabbage for Chelonis.
Enter the Grotto of Cursed Treasure
Find a cabbage without touching any treasure
I encountered a giant turtle named Chelonis that gave me a challenge: fetch him a cabbage from within a grotto, without touching a single piece of cursed treasure along the way.
Bring giant crab eggshells to Gorgo
I found four trophies from giant crab shells and brought them to Gorgo
Gorgo, the hunter trader at camp, will be interested in any special giant crab eggshells I can find.
I found several special giant crab eggshells and brought them to Gorgo so she can have a trophy from her voyage
Get a shell from the large eggs
Get a shell from the large eggs
Get a shell from the large eggs
Get a shell from the large eggs
A friendly ichthian named Teeth-Like-Spikes asked me to free him from his prison in the Ichthian Stronghold.
I freed Teeth-Like-Spikes from his prison in the Ichthian Stronghold
Kill the jailer for the cage key
I found Queen Erana\'s golden hoard
I learned of some golden skulls that can be used to gain access to ancient treasure when gathered.
I gathered the golden skulls and uncovered the ancient hoard of treasure, defeating its undead guardians in the process.
Return all skulls to their places to access the hoard
I found a treasure map with clues
A blind ichthian named Eyes-of-Pearl wants to bargain with me.
A blind ichthian named Eyes-of-Pearl tried to trick me, but I defeated him.
Three members of the shipwrecked crew have been lost amongst the eastern beaches. I should try to find them.
I found Hippias, Clio and Deon. After washing ashore, they ate enchanted food that turned them into pigs. I broke the spells and helped them back to camp.
Talk to the deckhands back at camp
Find out what the bird wants
A musician named Sosicles asked me to help rescue a siren that has been captured, since he\'s hoping to learn her song.
I rescued the siren and learned that her kind have been killed and captured by Nemesis. She shared a magical song, which blessed me.
Get the brothers to return to camp
I got the brothers to return to camp
Koritto asked me to find two brothers, Callimachus and Dolon, who were sent out to scout for food but didn\'t return.
The treasure at the top of the mountain was a trap set by a human-hating gryphon, but I defeated it and ensured Callimachus and Dolon made it safely back to camp.
Meet Koritto and the brothers in camp
Two members of the shipwrecked crew, Callimachus and Dolon, are hunting for treasure in the mountains. I\'d be helping out the crew if I can convince them to return after we find the treasure.
